<subSubSection id="A1A7BA8A2450FFFBFF490273FEEA8640" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="E902E9012450FFFBFF490273FE928231" blockId="16.[222,353,566,591]" box="[222,353,566,591]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="DBC935132450FFFBFF490273FE928231" bold="true" box="[222,353,566,591]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E902E9012450FFFBFF4902C4FDC483BA" blockId="16.[221,1112,641,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Broad, cylindraceous shell with elongated spire, shiny, reaching about 
<quantity id="2E4544E42450FFFBFB9402C4FBA282E7" box="[1027,1105,641,665]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
in length. Teleoconch consists of 8 to 10 slightly convex whorls. Spire outline straight to slightly concave, 16 to 18 regularly positioned axial ribs on all whorls, sometimes flattened on dorsal side of body whorl, spiral striae on the whole shell. Suture well defined, slightly undulated. Aperture shorter than half the entire shell, lirate inside. Lip straight in posterior half, then recurved towards the siphonal fasciole. Siphonal canal short and slightly recurved. Columella with 4 strong folds, decreasing in size anteriorly and merging into spiral cords on the siphonal fasciole.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E902E9012450FFFBFE940394FEB9844A" blockId="16.[221,1112,641,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Colour pattern: Shell dark red to orange. Protoconch and first whorls sometimes darker, columellar folds greyish, columellar shield and aperture shell coloured.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E902E9012450FFFBFE930404FE388400" blockId="16.[221,1112,641,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<materialsCitation id="59D5E35C2450FFFBFE930404FE388400" collectionCode="NMW" collectorName="Melvill-Tomlin &amp; E. R. Shopland &amp; J. C. Melvill" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="360657A32450FFFBFE930404FE9D8427" box="[260,366,1089,1113]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Holotype</typeStatus>
: 
<collectionCode id="8FAC71C42450FFFBFEE00404FE468427" box="[375,437,1089,1113]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">NMW</collectionCode>
.1955.158.00429 (coll. 
<collectorName id="44488CD72450FFFBFD390404FCBE8427" box="[686,845,1089,1113]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Melvill-Tomlin</collectorName>
), ex coll. 
<collectorName id="44488CD72450FFFBFC380404FBBC8427" box="[943,1103,1089,1113]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E.R. Shopland</collectorName>
; 
<collectorName id="44488CD72450FFFBFF490423FEAA8400" box="[222,345,1126,1150]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">J.C. Melvill</collectorName>
; 
<quantity id="2E4544E42450FFFBFEF50423FE348400" box="[354,455,1126,1150]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.88" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="18.8">18.8 mm</quantity>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E902E9012450FFFBFE9504C9FD3C84DA" blockId="16.[221,1112,641,1598]" box="[258,719,1164,1188]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Type locality: Arabian Sea, 
<collectingCountry id="91AAA9912450FFFBFDA304C9FD7784DA" box="[564,644,1164,1188]" name="Yemen" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Yemen</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="2B7927E32450FFFBFD1A04C9FD3884DA" box="[653,715,1164,1188]" country="Yemen" name="'Adan" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Aden</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E902E9012450FFFBFE9304F4FCC985FA" blockId="16.[221,1112,641,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Distribution: From the Red Sea (Gulf of Aqaba) in the north (
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFC2604F4FEB88490" author="Wils, E. &amp; Verbinnen, G." pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="21 - 39" refId="ref13021" refString="Wils, E. &amp; Verbinnen, G. (2002): Red Sea Mollusca Part 12: Costellariidae. - Gloria Maris 41 (1 - 2): 21 - 39." type="journal article" year="2002">Wils &amp; Verbinnen 2002</bibRefCitation>
) via the Arabian Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFDDC0493FD298490" author="Melvill, J. C." box="[587,730,1238,1262]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="221 - 223" refId="ref12319" refString="Melvill, J. C. (1895): Descriptions of new species of Pleurotoma, Mitra and Latirus. - Proceedings of the Malacological Society of London 1 (5): 221 - 223." type="journal article" year="1895">Melvill 1895</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="91AAA9912450FFFBFC890493FC428490" box="[798,945,1238,1262]" name="Mozambique" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="91AAA9912450FFFBFC400493FBC78490" box="[983,1076,1238,1262]" name="Réunion" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Réunion</collectingCountry>
in the south (
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFEC204B9FDB3856A" author="Robin, A. &amp; Martin, J. - C." box="[341,576,1276,1300]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref12575" refString="Robin, A. &amp; Martin, J. - C. (2004): Mitridae Costellariidae. - 34 pp., 64 plates, Hackenheim." type="book" year="2004">Robin &amp; Martin 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The species is also reported from the western Pacific: 
<collectingCountry id="91AAA9912450FFFBFEA00564FE868547" box="[311,373,1313,1337]" name="Japan" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFE150564FDED8547" author="Okutani, T." box="[386,542,1313,1337]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref12357" refString="Okutani, T. (2000): Marine Mollusks in Japan. - 1173 pp., Tokyo." type="book" year="2000">Okutani 2000</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="91AAA9912450FFFBFDA10564FD428547" box="[566,689,1313,1337]" name="Philippines" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(Schepmann 1911 – Figs 42–43) and 
<collectingCountry id="91AAA9912450FFFBFF490503FED78520" box="[222,292,1350,1374]" name="Guam" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Guam</collectingCountry>
. Further investigation is necessary to prove whether those specimens also belong to this species or to a closely related one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E902E9012450FFFBFE9405D4FEEA8640" blockId="16.[221,1112,641,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Remarks: This species was often put into synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="2EBD92822450FFFBFC0A05D4FD8C85B0" authority="(REEVE, 1845)" authorityName="Herrmann &amp; Stossier &amp; Salisbury" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="REEVE" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="corallinum" status="comb. nov." subGenus="Protoelongata">
<emphasis id="DBC935132450FFFBFC0A05D4FC0D85D7" box="[925,1022,1425,1449]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Vexillum</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="DBC935132450FFFBFB8705D4FEB685B0" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Protoelongata</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="DBC935132450FFFBFECF05F3FE2085B0" box="[344,467,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">corallinum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFE7205F3FD8685B0" author="Reeve, L. A." box="[485,629,1462,1486]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref12476" refString="Reeve, L. A. (1845): Monograph of the genus Mitra. Vol. 2. - London." type="book" year="1845">REEVE, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C0FA88682450FFFBFD1F05F3FCFB85B0" box="[648,776,1462,1486]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFC8005F3FC4A85B0" author="Okutani, T." box="[791,953,1462,1486]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref12357" refString="Okutani, T. (2000): Marine Mollusks in Japan. - 1173 pp., Tokyo." type="book" year="2000">Okutani 2000</bibRefCitation>
) or 
<taxonomicName id="2EBD92822450FFFBFC7905F3FD8E858A" authority="(ANTON, 1838)" baseAuthorityName="ANTON" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="semicostatum" subGenus="Pusia">
<emphasis id="DBC935132450FFFBFC7905F3FBA285B0" box="[1006,1105,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Vexillum</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="DBC935132450FFFBFF710599FED0858A" box="[230,291,1500,1524]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pusia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="DBC935132450FFFBFEA20599FE22858A" box="[309,465,1500,1524]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">semicostatum</emphasis>
(ANTON, 1838)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFD1C0599FCE6858A" author="Turner, H." box="[651,789,1500,1524]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="31 - 62" refId="ref12793" refString="Turner, H. (1989): Ungewohnliche und neue Mitroidea aus dem Indopazifik (Teil 1). - Club Conchylia Informationen 22 (5 - 6): 31 - 62." type="journal article" year="1989">Turner 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFCB20599FCA8858A" author="Turner, H." box="[805,859,1500,1524]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="3 - 31" refId="ref12861" refString="Turner, H. (1997): Three new species of mitriform gastropods with an illustrated check-list of the species living in the Red Sea. - Argonauta 10 (1 - 6): 3 - 31." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
, 2001; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D2C94F02450FFFBFC240599FEB98667" author="Wils, E. &amp; Verbinnen, G." pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="21 - 39" refId="ref13021" refString="Wils, E. &amp; Verbinnen, G. (2002): Red Sea Mollusca Part 12: Costellariidae. - Gloria Maris 41 (1 - 2): 21 - 39." type="journal article" year="2002">Wils &amp; Verbinnen 2002</bibRefCitation>
), but is easy to distinguish from those species by the missing white dots.
</paragraph>
